[
    {
        "content": "<p>This came up when discussing match syntax, but I'm splitting it into a new thread cuz this problem already exists in functions.</p>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"461444\">Sam Mohr</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/304641-ideas/topic/.60match.60.20without.20.60-.3E.60/near/501011063\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">match</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nf\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Blue</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Red</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Green</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Yellow</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div><br>\n</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>If you can use any pattern in a function, and you use the pattern <code>Blue | Red</code>, then your function definition looks like <code>| Pattern1 | Pattern2 | Result</code> which isn't good.</p>\n<p>In practice it's unlikely to come up for function defintions because <code>| Tag1 | Tag2 |</code> is not a very useful way to define a function, but if we're allowing any arbitrary pattern in a function definition, it should still be allowed.</p>\n<p>It would be much more likely to come up if we reused the syntax for patterns in matches.</p>\n<p>Will this be a problem, and how should it be fixed?</p>",
        "id": 501012018,
        "sender_full_name": "Sky Rose",
        "timestamp": 1740107332
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Option 1: Use <code>or</code> instead of <code>|</code> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/304641-ideas/topic/.E2.9C.94.20.60or.60.20instead.20of.20.60.7C.60.20in.20.60when.60.20branches\">#ideas &gt; ✔ &#96;or&#96; instead of &#96;|&#96; in &#96;when&#96; branches</a>  , but that idea was rejected already</p>",
        "id": 501012132,
        "sender_full_name": "Sky Rose",
        "timestamp": 1740107405
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>What if we used <code>+</code> for patterns? <code>| Red + Blue |</code>.</p>\n<p>This matches the academic idea of sum types, seems simple, and is otherwise unused in patterns, but would be unfamiliar to most people.</p>",
        "id": 501012337,
        "sender_full_name": "Sky Rose",
        "timestamp": 1740107524
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This topic was moved here from <a class=\"stream-topic\" data-stream-id=\"304641\" href=\"/#narrow/channel/304641-ideas/topic/.02klzzwxh.3A0000.03.20ambiguity.20in.20function.20defintion\">#ideas &gt; <code>|</code> ambiguity in function defintion</a> by <span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"607308\">Sky Rose</span>.</p>",
        "id": 501013699,
        "sender_full_name": "Notification Bot",
        "timestamp": 1740108467
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I prefer <code>or</code> because:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>it reads exactly the way you'd say it out loud</li>\n<li>we already have an <code>or</code> keyword</li>\n</ul>",
        "id": 501013928,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1740108629
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">get_user_email</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">|</span><span class=\"kt\">Admin</span><span class=\"p\">({</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">email</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">..</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">})</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Guest</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">email</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"nf\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">email</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 501013939,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1740108643
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">get_user_email</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">|</span><span class=\"kt\">Admin</span><span class=\"p\">({</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">email</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">..</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">})</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">or</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Guest</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">email</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"nf\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">email</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 501013946,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1740108650
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think <code>or</code> implies \"one or the other\"</p>",
        "id": 501013965,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1740108663
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But <code>+</code> implies \"both\"</p>",
        "id": 501013978,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1740108670
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So I also lean <code>or</code></p>",
        "id": 501013989,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1740108682
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"thumbs up\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f44d\" role=\"img\" title=\"thumbs up\">:thumbs_up:</span> I still dislike a couple things about <code>or</code> (from the other thread), but it is a totally safe choice.</p>",
        "id": 501014620,
        "sender_full_name": "Sky Rose",
        "timestamp": 1740109093
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I actually kinda like zig's <code>,</code>, especially how it interacts with the formatter. Adding a trailing comma always formats multiline, and visa versa. Super easy and controllable.</p>",
        "id": 501019423,
        "sender_full_name": "Joshua Warner",
        "timestamp": 1740112518
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><del>I want to register my support for <code>,</code></del> Redacted after thinking about it in the context of Roc's pattern matching capabilities - which are MUCH richer than ZIg</p>",
        "id": 501082504,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1740137234
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Might be a little confusing with tuples and lists</p>",
        "id": 501082708,
        "sender_full_name": "Eli Dowling",
        "timestamp": 1740137302
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That's what I was just about to write</p>",
        "id": 501082725,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1740137310
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The problem is that alternatives internal to a collection would have to be surrounded by <code>()</code></p>",
        "id": 501082798,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1740137339
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But to flesh out the design space, the only other symbol that makes sense to use here is <code>^</code></p>",
        "id": 501083043,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1740137416
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">get_user_email</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">Admin</span><span class=\"p\">({</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">email</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">..</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">})</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Guest</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">email</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">email</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 501083084,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1740137428
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I guess <code>/</code> also has the connotation of \"either or\"</p>",
        "id": 501083222,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1740137478
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">get_user_email</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">Admin</span><span class=\"p\">({</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">email</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">..</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">})</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Guest</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">email</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">email</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 501083279,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1740137503
    },
